President Trump and Vice President Pence, along with other government officials, hosted a Made in America Roundtable at the White House. The roundtable included 20 companies that manufacture their products in the United States. The purpose of the event was to highlight the importance of manufacturing products in American factories using American workers. The Trump Administration officials and Congressmen discussed ways to support and promote American manufacturing. This event is part of the White House's Made in America Week, which also included a Made in America Product Showcase.